1️⃣ Export locally from Workbench

Open Workbench → Server → Data Export

Select your database (va-disabilities)

Choose Export to Self-Contained File

Save the SQL file locally, e.g., C:\Users\gianu\Desktop\va-disabilities.sql

2️⃣ Import via SSH (existing method)

Since remote Workbench connection won’t work, use the existing SSH + MySQL session to import:

mysql -u root -p va-disabilities


Then inside MySQL:

SOURCE /root/va-disabilities.sql;


You already did this before and it worked, so this is safe.

✅ Key point

Without sudo/root access, Workbench cannot connect directly to the server’s MySQL because:

bind-address is still 127.0.0.1

Firewall may block port 3306

So your best workflow is:

Export locally from Workbench → .sql file

SCP the file to the server

Log in via SSH → import using SOURCE

