Perfect — that’s your new dump file. Here’s how to get it onto the server and import it safely via SSH/MySQL, step by step:

1️⃣ Copy the dump to the server

From PowerShell on your local machine:

scp "C:\Users\gianu\OneDrive\Documents\dumps\Dump20250829.sql" root@67.205.168.90:/root/


This places the file at /root/Dump20250829.sql on the server.

2️⃣ SSH into the server
ssh root@67.205.168.90

3️⃣ Import the dump into MySQL

Log into MySQL:

mysql -u root -p


Inside the MySQL prompt:

DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS `va-disabilities`;
CREATE DATABASE `va-disabilities`;
USE `va-disabilities`;
SOURCE /root/Dump20250829.sql;


This will replace the old database completely with your new dump.

4️⃣ Verify the import
SHOW TABLES;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM va_disabilities;
SELECT * FROM va_disabilities LIMIT 5;


Make sure the table va_disabilities exists and the data is present, including the new “Breathing difficulties (diaphragmatic respiration)” entry.
